03/11/76   edit explain, edit exp

Function:  The explain request prints an online description of a
specified edit request.  If no argument is supplied, general
information about the edit command is listed.  See also the explain
command in Section IV of the M__u_l_t_i_c_s D_F_A_S_T_ S__u_b_s_y_s_t_e_m U__s_e_r_s'_ G__u_i_d_e 
(order No. AT59).



Syntax:  edit explain {-long} request1{ request2 ... requestN}


where:

1.   -long       is a control argument that specifies a long form of
                 explain messages for given requests; if not supplied,
                 a brief message is printed.

2.   requesti    can be selected from the current set of edit requests.


